{"id":732,"date":"2022-09-07T11:28:18","date_gmt":"2022-09-07T10:28:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/parents\/help-and-support\/keeping-safe\/"},"modified":"2023-06-26T14:21:29","modified_gmt":"2023-06-26T13:21:29","slug":"keeping-safe","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/parents\/help-and-support\/keeping-safe\/","title":{"rendered":"Keeping Safe"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile\" style=\"grid-template-columns:16% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.nspcc.org.uk\/keeping-children-safe\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"134\" height=\"49\" src=\"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2022\/09\/nspcc.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-757 size-full\" \/><\/a><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Support and tips to help you keep children safe. From advice on children\u2019s mental health to staying safe online, support for parents and what to do if you\u2019re worried about a child.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile\" style=\"grid-template-columns:16% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.childline.org.uk\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"189\" height=\"53\" src=\"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2022\/09\/childline.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-760 size-full\" \/><\/a><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Childline is yours \u2013 a free, private and confidential service where you can talk about anything. We\u2019re here for you online, on the phone, anytime.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile\" style=\"grid-template-columns:16% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.thinkuknow.co.uk\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"174\" height=\"105\" src=\"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2022\/09\/ceop.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-763 size-full\" \/><\/a><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The National Crime Agency&#8217;s CEOP Education team aim to help protect children and young people from online child sexual abuse.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile\" style=\"grid-template-columns:16% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.birminghamchildrenstrust.co.uk\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"230\" height=\"52\" src=\"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2022\/09\/bct.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-781 size-full\" \/><\/a><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The Birmingham Children\u2019s Trust exists to make a positive difference for children, young people and families in the city.  <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.birminghamchildrenstrust.co.uk\/info\/6\/contact_us\/38\/worried_about_a_child\">If you&#8217;re worried about a child, contact us | Worried about a child? | Birmingham Children&#8217;s Trust (birminghamchildrenstrust.co.uk)<\/a><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile\" style=\"grid-template-columns:15% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.hestia.org\/brightsky\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"79\" height=\"59\" src=\"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2022\/10\/bright-sky.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1133 size-full\" \/><\/a><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p>If you are concerned about domestic abuse, we know it can be hard to find support. That\u2019s why Bright Sky was developed.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bright Sky is a safe, easy to use app and&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/uk.bright-sky.org\/en\/home\">website<\/a>&nbsp;that provides practical support and information on how to respond to domestic abuse. It is for anyone experiencing domestic abuse, or who is worried about someone else.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bright Sky helps you to spot the signs of abuse, know how to respond, and help someone find a safe route to support.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile\" style=\"grid-template-columns:15% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><a href=\"https:\/\/hollieguard.com\/#whatishollieguard\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"84\" height=\"81\" src=\"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2022\/10\/hollie-guard-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1138 size-full\" \/><\/a><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p>In danger? Hollie Guard is a next generation smartphone app that provides enhanced levels of protection. With a simple shake or tap, Hollie Guard, immediately notifies your chosen contacts, pinpointing your location and sending audio and video evidence directly to their mobile phones.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Support and tips to help you keep children safe. From advice on children\u2019s mental health to staying safe online, support for parents and what to do if you\u2019re worried about a child. Childline is yours \u2013 a free, private and confidential service where you can talk about anything. We\u2019re here for you online, on the phone, anytime. The National Crime Agency&#8217;s CEOP Education team aim to help protect children and young people from online child sexual abuse. The Birmingham Children\u2019s [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":7,"featured_media":0,"parent":706,"menu_order":2,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-732","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"acf":{"sidebar":true,"landing_page":false},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/732"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/7"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=732"}],"version-history":[{"count":10,"href":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/732\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1139,"href":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/732\/revisions\/1139"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/706"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=732"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}